{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775893633375,"sessionID":"ses_2847e1defffeWSK7ukhgNKbnF7","part":{"id":"prt_d7b8255ba0011gkoW098qvcK5J","messageID":"msg_d7b8235ed00148Hfwiw5mLtVIc","sessionID":"ses_2847e1defffeWSK7ukhgNKbnF7","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-3a1953a83e1647baacabad395ce4d327","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-037/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-037/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-037 — PCAP 分析器示例应用\n2: \n3: **Module:** example  \n4: **Language:** Python  \n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: [TO BE FILLED: Add overview of PCAP 分析器示例应用]\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: [TO BE FILLED]\n18: \n19: [TO BE FILLED: Add requirement description]\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: [TO BE FILLED]\n22: \n23: - **GIVEN** [TO BE FILLED]\n24: - **WHEN** [TO BE FILLED]\n25: - **THEN** [TO BE FILLED]\n26: \n27: ---\n28: \n29: ## Constants Summary\n30: \n31: | Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n32: |----------|-------|------|---------|\n33: | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] |\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ## Dependencies Summary\n38: \n39: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n40: |---------|---------|---------|\n41: | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] |\n42: \n43: ---\n44: \n45: ## File Changes Summary\n46: \n47: | File | Action | Description |\n48: |------|--------|-------------|\n49: | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] |\n50: \n51: ---\n52: \n53: ## References\n54: \n55: - [TO BE FILLED: Add relevant references]\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ## Validation Checklist\n60: \n61: - [ ] [TO BE FILLED]\n\n(End of file - total 61 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-037 — PCAP 分析器示例应用\n\n**Module:** example  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\n[TO BE FILLED: Add overview of PCAP 分析器示例应用]\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: [TO BE FILLED]\n\n[TO BE FILLED: Add requirement description]\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-037/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775893633356,"end":1775893633374}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775893633377,"sessionID":"ses_2847e1defffeWSK7ukhgNKbnF7","part":{"id":"prt_d7b8255bc001dowl4e0pV8AYxl","messageID":"msg_d7b8235ed00148Hfwiw5mLtVIc","sessionID":"ses_2847e1defffeWSK7ukhgNKbnF7","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-fa3ea29ad0864bd7941a52c0de211e67","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-036/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-036/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-036 — Dify 插件集成\n2: \n3: **Module:** integrations  \n4: **Language:** Python  \n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Implement AgentCube Dify plugin integration providing code interpreter capabilities through a Dify-compatible Python plugin, plus a PCAP analyzer example demonstrating AgentCube sandbox orchestration with LangChain/LangGraph agents.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Dify plugin bootstrap and runtime\n18: \n19: The system SHALL expose a Dify-compatible Python plugin whose process entry runs the framework runner with a configured maximum request timeout.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Plugin process starts\n22: \n23: - **GIVEN** the plugin package is installed with compatible `dify-plugin` and `agentcube-sdk` versions\n24: - **WHEN** the platform starts the plugin using the manifest-declared entrypoint\n25: - **THEN** the plugin SHALL execute `main` which runs `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()` until the host stops it\n26: \n27: ---\n28: \n29: ### Requirement: Plugin manifest structure\n30: \n31: The system SHALL ship a root `manifest.yaml` declaring plugin metadata, tool provider registration, resource permissions, and runner metadata sufficient for Dify to load and execute the plugin.\n32: \n33: #### Scenario: Required manifest fields\n34: \n35: - **GIVEN** a valid plugin package root\n36: - **WHEN** the manifest is parsed by a Dify-compatible toolchain\n37: - **THEN** the manifest SHALL include `version`, `type: plugin`, `author`, `name`, `label` (multilingual map), `description` (multilingual), `icon`, `icon_dark`, `resource` (including `memory` and `permission` subtree), `plugins.tools` listing provider descriptors, and `meta` containing `version`, `arch`, `runner` (`language`, `version`, `entrypoint`), and `minimum_dify_version`\n38: \n39: #### Scenario: Tool provider wiring\n40: \n41: - **GIVEN** the manifest `plugins.tools` references the Agentcube provider descriptor\n42: - **WHEN** the plugin is loaded\n43: - **THEN** Dify SHALL resolve `provider/agentcube.yaml` and associate it with the Python module declared under `extra.python.source`\n44: \n45: ---\n46: \n47: ### Requirement: Provider descriptor structure\n48: \n49: The system SHALL define a tool provider YAML that identifies the provider, lists its tools, and points to the Python provider implementation.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: Provider lists tools and entry module\n52: \n53: - **GIVEN** `provider/agentcube.yaml` is present\n54: - **WHEN** the integration runtime resolves the provider\n55: - **THEN** the descriptor SHALL include `identity` (author, name, multilingual label/description, icon), a `tools` list including `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`, and `extra.python.source: provider/agentcube.py`\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ### Requirement: Tool parameter schema\n60: \n61: The system SHALL declare a tool schema for the code interpreter integration including connection endpoints, optional language selection, and code/command/session fields.\n62: \n63: #### Scenario: Declared parameters match remote APIs\n64: \n65: - **GIVEN** `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`\n66: - **WHEN** an operator configures the tool in Dify\n67: - **THEN** the schema SHALL require string parameters `router_url` and `workload_manager_url`, SHALL offer optional `language` as a select among `python`, `javascript`, and `typescript`, and SHALL allow optional `code`, `command`, `session_id`, `session_reuse` (boolean), and `code_interpreter_id`, each documented for human and LLM-oriented forms\n68: \n69: ---\n70: \n71: ### Requirement: Tool provider credential validation\n72: \n73: The system SHALL implement credential validation on the tool provider class and SHALL surface validation failures using the Dify tool provider error type.\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Invalid credentials are rejected\n76: \n77: - **GIVEN** an instance of `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider`\n78: - **WHEN** `_validate_credentials` encounters an error condition the implementer treats as invalid\n79: - **THEN** the provider SHALL raise `ToolProviderCredentialValidationError` with a string message derived from the failure\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: Successful validation completes quietly\n82: \n83: - **GIVEN** credentials that satisfy the provider's validation rules\n84: - **WHEN** `_validate_credentials` runs\n85: - **THEN** the method SHALL return without raising\n86: \n87: ---\n88: \n89: ### Requirement: Tool invocation and JSON messaging\n90: \n91: The system SHALL implement the Agentcube code interpreter tool as a Dify `Tool` that delegates execution and returns structured JSON to the host.\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: Dify invokes the tool\n94: \n95: - **GIVEN** a configured tool invocation with parameters matching the schema\n96: - **WHEN** Dify calls `_invoke` on `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool`\n97: - **THEN** the tool SHALL call `execute(**tool_parameters)` and SHALL yield `create_json_message(result)` for the outcome\n98: \n99: ---\n100: \n101: ### Requirement: Tool execution API surface\n102: \n103: The system SHALL implement `execute` with parameters for router and workload manager URLs, optional language, session controls, and code or command execution, delegating to `agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient`.\n104: \n105: #### Scenario: Code or command runs against configured endpoints\n106: \n107: - **GIVEN** valid `router_url`, `workload_manager_url`, and optional `language` defaulting to `python`\n108: - **WHEN** the tool receives `code` and/or `command` with optional `session_id`, `session_reuse`, and `code_interpreter_id`\n109: - **THEN** the tool SHALL use the AgentCube Python SDK client to perform the corresponding remote operations and SHALL return a JSON-serializable result object suitable for `create_json_message`\n110: \n111: ---\n112: \n113: ### Requirement: Plugin Python dependencies\n114: \n115: The system SHALL pin compatible versions of `dify-plugin` and `agentcube-sdk` for reproducible installs.\n116: \n117: #### Scenario: Dependency bounds\n118: \n119: - **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/requirements.txt`\n120: - **WHEN** dependencies are installed in a clean environment\n121: - **THEN** installs SHALL satisfy `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0` and `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10`\n122: \n123: ---\n124: \n125: ### Requirement: PCAP analyzer FastAPI service\n126: \n127: The system SHALL provide a FastAPI application that validates OpenAI-compatible configuration at startup, composes LangChain/LangGraph agents, and exposes an analysis endpoint for PCAP uploads.\n128: \n129: #### Scenario: Startup requires API key\n130: \n131: - **GIVEN** the process is started without a usable `OPENAI_API_KEY` (or equivalent configured API key)\n132: - **WHEN** the application completes startup hooks\n133: - **THEN** startup SHALL fail rather than serve requests without credentials\n134: \n135: #### Scenario: Analyze endpoint accepts PCAP input\n136: \n137: - **GIVEN** a running service with valid LLM configuration\n138: - **WHEN** a client calls `POST /analyze` with either an uploaded PCAP file or a `pcap_path` form field\n139: - **THEN** the handler SHALL return a body matching `AnalyzeResponse` including `script`, `results`, and `report`\n140: \n141: ---\n142: \n143: ### Requirement: PCAP analyzer configuration surface\n144: \n145: The system SHALL read runtime configuration from environment variables for the OpenAI-compatible API, model selection, and AgentCube sandbox parameters.\n146: \n147: #### Scenario: Defaults and overrides\n148: \n149: - **GIVEN** standard deployment environment variables\n150: - **WHEN** the service starts\n151: - **THEN** it SHALL use `OPENAI_API_BASE` defaulting to `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1`, `OPENAI_MODEL` defaulting to `Qwen/QwQ-32B`, `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME` defaulting to `my-interpreter`, `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE` defaulting to `default`, and `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` defaulting to `5`, while binding HTTP to `0.0.0.0:8000` as defined in the application\n152: \n153: ---\n154: \n155: ### Requirement: PCAP analyzer sandbox integration\n156: \n157: The system SHALL orchestrate PCAP analysis by planning and repairing scripts, executing them inside an AgentCube-backed sandbox via `SandboxRunner`, and aggregating results through reporter agents.\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: Sandbox runner executes commands\n160: \n161: - **GIVEN** a `SandboxRunner` constructed with interpreter name, namespace, and warmup duration\n162: - **WHEN** analysis logic invokes `run` with a shell command\n163: - **THEN** the runner SHALL execute the command in the remote sandbox context and SHALL return structured execution results for downstream LLM steps\n164: \n165: #### Scenario: File staging uses runner uploads\n166: \n167: - **GIVEN** a local PCAP path or bytes to analyze\n168: - **WHEN** the orchestration needs the artifact inside the sandbox workspace\n169: - **THEN** the system SHALL use `upload_file` or `upload_bytes` on `SandboxRunner` before executing analysis commands\n170: \n171: ---\n172: \n173: ### Requirement: PCAP analyzer container image\n174: \n175: The system SHALL build a container image that installs Python dependencies with `uv`, vendors the in-repo `agentcube` SDK copy, sets `PYTHONPATH`, exposes port 8000, and starts the FastAPI app via `uv run`.\n176: \n177: #### Scenario: Image entrypoint\n178: \n179: - **GIVEN** the `example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile` build context\n180: - **WHEN** the container runs without overriding the command\n181: - **THEN** the default command SHALL be `uv run pcap_analyzer.py` with `PYTHONPATH=\"/app\"` and port `8000` exposed\n182: \n183: ---\n184: \n185: ### Requirement: PCAP analyzer Kubernetes deployment\n186: \n187: The system SHALL supply a `Deployment` manifest that runs the analyzer image with resource requests/limits and environment variables wired from a Secret and plain env for AgentCube and model endpoints.\n188: \n189: #### Scenario: Deployment wiring\n190: \n191: - **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/deployment.yaml` applied to the cluster\n192: - **WHEN** the workload becomes ready\n193: - **THEN** the pod SHALL run image `pcap-analyzer:latest` (pull `IfNotPresent`), listen on TCP 8000, request `cpu: 200m` / `memory: 100Mi` and limit `cpu: 1` / `memory: 1Gi`, mount `OPENAI_API_KEY` from Secret `pcap-analyzer-secrets` key `openai-api-key`, and set `OPENAI_API_BASE`, `OPENAI_MODEL`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL`, `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME`, `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE`, and `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` as container environment variables\n194: \n195: #### Scenario: Process launch in cluster\n196: \n197: - **GIVEN** the deployment's container specification\n198: - **WHEN** Kubernetes starts the container\n199: - **THEN** the command SHALL be `uv` with arguments `run pcap_analyzer.py`, matching local Docker behavior\n200: \n201: ---\n202: \n203: ## Constants Summary\n204: \n205: | Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n206: |----------|-------|------|---------|\n207: | `MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT` | `120` | `main.py` | Plugin request timeout |\n208: | `SERVER_HOST` | `0.0.0.0` | `pcap_analyzer.py` | HTTP bind address |\n209: | `SERVER_PORT` | `8000` | `pcap_analyzer.py` | HTTP port |\n210: | `SERVER_RELOAD` | `True` | `pcap_analyzer.py` | Development reload flag |\n211: | `manifest.version` | `0.0.2` | `manifest.yaml` | Plugin version |\n212: | `meta.runner.language` | `python` | `manifest.yaml` | Runner language |\n213: | `meta.runner.version` | `3.12` | `manifest.yaml` | Python version |\n214: | `meta.runner.entrypoint` | `main` | `manifest.yaml` | Entry module |\n215: \n216: ---\n217: \n218: ## Dependencies Summary\n219: \n220: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n221: |---------|---------|---------|\n222: | `dify-plugin` | `>=0.4.2,<0.5.0` | Dify plugin framework |\n223: | `agentcube-sdk` | `>=0.0.10` | AgentCube client SDK |\n224: | `fastapi` | `0.120.0` | PCAP analyzer web framework |\n225: | `uvicorn` | `0.38.0` | ASGI server |\n226: | `langchain` | `1.0.2` | LLM orchestration |\n227: | `langchain-openai` | `1.0.1` | OpenAI integration |\n228: | `langgraph` | `1.0.1` | Agent graphs |\n229: | `langgraph-prebuilt` | `1.0.1` | Prebuilt agents |\n230: | `python-multipart` | `0.0.20` | File upload support |\n231: \n232: ---\n233: \n234: ## File Changes Summary\n235: \n236: ### Dify Plugin (`integrations/dify-plugin/`)\n237: \n238: | File | Action | Description |\n239: |------|--------|-------------|\n240: | `main.py` | create | Plugin entry: `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()` |\n241: | `manifest.yaml` | create | Root manifest with metadata, tools list, runner config |\n242: | `provider/agentcube.yaml` | create | Provider descriptor with identity and tools list |\n243: | `provider/agentcube.py` | create | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider` credential validation |\n244: | `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` | create | Tool parameter schema |\n245: | `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py` | create | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool` implementation |\n246: | `requirements.txt` | create | `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0`, `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10` |\n247: | `GUIDE.md` | create | Usage documentation |\n248: | `README.md` | create | Plugin overview |\n249: | `PRIVACY.md` | create | Privacy policy |\n250: | `.difyignore` | create | Packaging exclusion rules |\n251: | `icon.png` | create | Light theme icon |\n252: | `icon-dark.png` | create | Dark theme icon |\n253: \n254: ### PCAP Analyzer (`example/pcap-analyzer/`)\n255: \n256: | File | Action | Description |\n257: |------|--------|-------------|\n258: | `pcap_analyzer.py` | create | FastAPI app with agents, SandboxRunner, /analyze endpoint |\n259: | `requirements.txt` | create | FastAPI, LangChain, LangGraph dependencies |\n260: | `Dockerfile` | create | `uv`-based image with vendored agentcube SDK |\n261: | `deployment.yaml` | create | K8s Deployment with Secret and env wiring |\n262: | `README.md` | create | Documentation |\n263: \n264: ---\n265: \n266: ## References\n267: \n268: - integrations/design.md — Architecture and file map\n269: - integrations/spec.md — Normative requirements\n270: - python-sdk/design.md — AgentCube SDK design\n271: - python-sdk/spec.md — AgentCube SDK specification\n272: - proposal.md — AR-036 proposal\n273: \n274: ---\n275: \n276: ## Validation Checklist\n277: \n278: - [ ] Plugin starts and runs with `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()`\n279: - [ ] `manifest.yaml` includes all required fields\n280: - [ ] Provider descriptor lists tools and Python entry\n281: - [ ] Tool schema declares all parameters correctly\n282: - [ ] Credential validation raises `ToolProviderCredentialValidationError` on failure\n283: - [ ] Tool invocation yields JSON message via `create_json_message`\n284: - [ ] Dependencies satisfy version bounds\n285: - [ ] PCAP analyzer fails startup without API key\n286: - [ ] `/analyze` endpoint returns `AnalyzeResponse`\n287: - [ ] SandboxRunner executes commands in remote context\n288: - [ ] Dockerfile runs `uv run pcap_analyzer.py`\n289: - [ ] Deployment manifest wires environment correctly\n\n(End of file - total 289 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-036 — Dify 插件集成\n\n**Module:** integrations  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nImplement AgentCube Dify plugin integration providing code interpreter capabilities through a Dify-compatible Python plugin, plus a PCAP analyzer example demonstrating AgentCube sandbox orchestration with LangChain/LangGraph agents.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: Dify plugin bootstrap and runtime\n\nThe system SHALL expose a Dify-compatible Python plugin whose process entry runs the framework runner with a configured maximum request timeout.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-036/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775893633361,"end":1775893633376}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775893633380,"sessionID":"ses_2847e1defffeWSK7ukhgNKbnF7","part":{"id":"prt_d7b82592c001P6cAisXjbaaiR7","messageID":"msg_d7b8235ed00148Hfwiw5mLtVIc","sessionID":"ses_2847e1defffeWSK7ukhgNKbnF7","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-36b37a9ad50c4ffcaf127f735812ea82","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sdk-python/examples/agent_runtime_usage.py"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sdk-python/examples/agent_runtime_usage.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: #!/usr/bin/env python3\n2: \"\"\"\n3: AgentRuntimeClient Usage Example\n4: \n5: This script demonstrates how to use the AgentRuntimeClient to:\n6: 1. Bootstrap a session\n7: 2. Invoke an agent with a payload\n8: 3. Handle responses\n9: \"\"\"\n10: \n11: import argparse\n12: import os\n13: import sys\n14: \n15: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n16: \n17: \n18: def main():\n19:     parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\"AgentRuntimeClient Usage Example\")\n20:     parser.add_argument(\"--agent-name\", required=True, help=\"Agent name to invoke\")\n21:     parser.add_argument(\"--namespace\", default=\"default\", help=\"Kubernetes namespace\")\n22:     parser.add_argument(\"--router-url\", help=\"Router URL (or use ROUTER_URL env var)\")\n23:     parser.add_argument(\"--verbose\", action=\"store_true\", help=\"Enable verbose logging\")\n24:     parser.add_argument(\"--timeout\", type=int, default=120, help=\"Read timeout in seconds\")\n25:     parser.add_argument(\"--session-id\", help=\"Existing session ID to reuse\")\n26:     parser.add_argument(\n27:         \"--payload\",\n28:         default='{\"action\": \"test\"}',\n29:         help=\"JSON payload to send to agent\",\n30:     )\n31:     \n32:     args = parser.parse_args()\n33:     \n34:     router_url = args.router_url or os.environ.get(\"ROUTER_URL\")\n35:     if not router_url:\n36:         print(\"Error: Router URL must be provided via --router-url or ROUTER_URL env var\")\n37:         sys.exit(1)\n38:     \n39:     try:\n40:         with AgentRuntimeClient(\n41:             agent_name=args.agent_name,\n42:             namespace=args.namespace,\n43:             router_url=router_url,\n44:             verbose=args.verbose,\n45:             session_id=args.session_id,\n46:             timeout=args.timeout,\n47:         ) as client:\n48:             print(f\"Session ID: {client.session_id}\")\n49:             \n50:             payload = eval(args.payload)\n51:             print(f\"Invoking agent with payload: {payload}\")\n52:             \n53:             result = client.invoke(payload)\n54:             print(f\"Result: {result}\")\n55:             \n56:     except ValueError as e:\n57:         print(f\"Error: {e}\")\n58:         sys.exit(1)\n59:     except Exception as e:\n60:         print(f\"Unexpected error: {e}\")\n61:         sys.exit(1)\n62: \n63: \n64: if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n65:     main()\n\n(End of file - total 65 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nAgentRuntimeClient Usage Example\n\nThis script demonstrates how to use the AgentRuntimeClient to:\n1. Bootstrap a session\n2. Invoke an agent with a payload\n3. Handle responses\n\"\"\"\n\nimport argparse\nimport os\nimport sys\n\nfrom agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n\n\ndef main():\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\"AgentRuntimeClient Usage Example\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--agent-name\", required=True, help=\"Agent name to invoke\")","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sdk-python/examples/agent_runtime_usage.py","time":{"start":1775893633363,"end":1775893633378}}}}
