{"type":"text","timestamp":1775893736977,"sessionID":"ses_2847e1defffeWSK7ukhgNKbnF7","part":{"id":"prt_d7b82c6c30010g0HHbVxZNXV6p","messageID":"msg_d7b8297df001ybeISC5tz5hkvv","sessionID":"ses_2847e1defffeWSK7ukhgNKbnF7","type":"text","text":"Now I have all the context needed. I'll write the delta-spec.md for AR-037 — PCAP 分析器示例应用:","time":{"start":1775893736973,"end":1775893736973}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775893737071,"sessionID":"ses_2847e1defffeWSK7ukhgNKbnF7","part":{"id":"prt_d7b83ee120019dO1OsE0g37HZd","messageID":"msg_d7b8297df001ybeISC5tz5hkvv","sessionID":"ses_2847e1defffeWSK7ukhgNKbnF7","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-f8d1ed70d2ad440daf2a53fcf4609c5b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-037/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Spec: AR-037 — PCAP 分析器示例应用\n\n**Module:** example  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nA standalone PCAP analyzer example application demonstrating AgentCube sandbox orchestration with LangChain/LangGraph agents. This FastAPI service uploads PCAP files to an AgentCube sandbox, uses an LLM to plan and repair analysis scripts, executes them remotely, and generates structured analysis reports.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: FastAPI service bootstrap\n\nThe system SHALL provide a FastAPI application that validates OpenAI-compatible API configuration at startup and builds ReAct agents for script planning and report generation.\n\n#### Scenario: Startup validates API key\n\n- **GIVEN** the FastAPI application is initializing\n- **WHEN** the startup event handler executes without a valid `OPENAI_API_KEY` environment variable\n- **THEN** the application SHALL raise `RuntimeError(\"OPENAI_API_KEY is required at startup\")` and SHALL NOT begin serving requests\n\n#### Scenario: Startup builds LLM client\n\n- **GIVEN** a valid `OPENAI_API_KEY` is present\n- **WHEN** the startup event handler completes\n- **THEN** the application SHALL instantiate `ChatOpenAI` with `api_key`, `base_url` (from `OPENAI_API_BASE` defaulting to `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1`), and `model_name` (from `OPENAI_MODEL` defaulting to `Qwen/QwQ-32B`)\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Analyze endpoint interface\n\nThe system SHALL expose a `POST /analyze` endpoint accepting PCAP file uploads or local path references and returning structured analysis results.\n\n#### Scenario: Analyze with uploaded file\n\n- **GIVEN** a client sends `POST /analyze` with multipart `pcap_file` upload\n- **WHEN** the request reaches the handler\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL read the file bytes, stage them in the sandbox via `SandboxRunner.upload_bytes`, orchestrate analysis with retries, and return `AnalyzeResponse(script, results, report)`\n\n#### Scenario: Analyze with local path\n\n- **GIVEN** a client sends `POST /analyze` with form field `pcap_path` pointing to a local file\n- **WHEN** the request reaches the handler\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL upload the file via `SandboxRunner.upload_file`, orchestrate analysis with retries, and return `AnalyzeResponse(script, results, report)`\n\n#### Scenario: Missing input validation\n\n- **GIVEN** a client sends `POST /analyze` without `pcap_file` and without `pcap_path`\n- **WHEN** the request reaches the handler\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL raise `HTTPException(status_code=400, detail=\"Either pcap_file or pcap_path required\")`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: SandboxRunner orchestration\n\nThe system SHALL implement `SandboxRunner` that wraps `CodeInterpreterClient` to upload files and execute shell commands in the remote sandbox.\n\n#### Scenario: SandboxRunner initialization\n\n- **GIVEN** `SandboxRunner(name=\"my-interpreter\", namespace=\"default\", warmup_sec=5)`\n- **WHEN** the runner is constructed\n- **THEN** it SHALL create a `CodeInterpreterClient` with `router_url` from `ROUTER_URL` env, `workload_manager_url` from `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env, `name`, `namespace`, and `ttl` derived from `warmup_sec`\n\n#### Scenario: SandboxRunner file upload\n\n- **GIVEN** a `SandboxRunner` instance with active session\n- **WHEN** `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)` or `upload_bytes(data, remote_path)` is called\n- **THEN** the runner SHALL delegate to `CodeInterpreterClient.upload_file` or write base64-encoded content via `write_file` respectively\n\n#### Scenario: SandboxRunner command execution\n\n- **GIVEN** a `SandboxRunner` instance with staged files\n- **WHEN** `run(command)` is invoked\n- **THEN** the runner SHALL call `execute_command(command)` and SHALL return a dict with `stdout`, `stderr`, `exit_code`\n\n#### Scenario: SandboxRunner cleanup\n\n- **GIVEN** a `SandboxRunner` that has completed analysis\n- **WHEN** `stop()` is called\n- **THEN** the runner SHALL call `CodeInterpreterClient.stop()` to delete the control-plane session and close HTTP connections\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: LLM agent orchestration\n\nThe system SHALL use LangGraph ReAct agents for planning analysis scripts, repairing failed executions, and generating final reports.\n\n#### Scenario: Planner agent generates script\n\n- **GIVEN** the `PLANNER` ReAct agent built with `build_planner_agent(llm)`\n- **WHEN** `_plan_script(agent, pcap_path)` is called\n- **THEN** the agent SHALL receive a prompt describing the PCAP analysis task and SHALL return a Python script string for execution\n\n#### Scenario: Script execution with retry\n\n- **GIVEN** an initial script from the planner\n- **WHEN** `_execute_once_in_runner(runner, pcap_path, script)` returns non-zero `exit_code`\n- **THEN** `_analyze_with_retries` SHALL call `_repair_script(agent, prev_script, results)` to get a corrected script, and SHALL retry execution up to `max_retries` (default 2)\n\n#### Scenario: Reporter agent generates report\n\n- **GIVEN** successful execution results from `_execute_once_in_runner`\n- **WHEN** `_report(agent, results)` is called\n- **THEN** the `REPORTER` agent SHALL synthesize the execution outputs into a human-readable analysis report string\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Configuration via environment\n\nThe system SHALL read all runtime parameters from environment variables with documented defaults.\n\n#### Scenario: Default configuration values\n\n- **GIVEN** the application starts without custom environment overrides\n- **WHEN** globals are initialized\n- **THEN** `OPENAI_API_BASE` SHALL default to `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1`, `OPENAI_MODEL` to `Qwen/QwQ-32B`, `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME` to `my-interpreter`, `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE` to `default`, `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` to `5`\n\n#### Scenario: Server binding constants\n\n- **GIVEN** the FastAPI application\n- **WHEN** `uvicorn.run` is invoked in the main block\n- **THEN** it SHALL bind to `SERVER_HOST=\"0.0.0.0\"` and `SERVER_PORT=8000` with `SERVER_RELOAD=True` for development\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Container image construction\n\nThe system SHALL provide a Dockerfile that builds a minimal container with `uv`-managed dependencies and vendored SDK.\n\n#### Scenario: Dockerfile base and deps\n\n- **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile` build context\n- **WHEN** `docker build` runs\n- **THEN** the image SHALL use `ghcr.io/astral-sh/uv:python3.12-bookworm-slim` base, SHALL create a venv with `uv venv`, SHALL install `requirements.txt` packages with `uv pip install`, and SHALL copy `agentcube` SDK from `sdk-python/agentcube` to `/app/agentcube`\n\n#### Scenario: Dockerfile runtime config\n\n- **GIVEN** the built container image\n- **WHEN** the container starts\n- **THEN** `PYTHONPATH=\"/app\"` SHALL be set, port `8000` SHALL be exposed, and the default command SHALL be `[\"uv\", \"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Kubernetes deployment manifest\n\nThe system SHALL supply a Deployment manifest with resource constraints, secret mounting, and environment wiring.\n\n#### Scenario: Deployment resource limits\n\n- **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/deployment.yaml`\n- **WHEN** the manifest is applied to a Kubernetes cluster\n- **THEN** the container SHALL request `cpu: 200m` and `memory: 100Mi`, and SHALL limit to `cpu: 1` and `memory: 1Gi`\n\n#### Scenario: Secret mounting for API key\n\n- **GIVEN** the deployment container spec\n- **WHEN** the pod starts\n- **THEN** `OPENAI_API_KEY` SHALL be mounted from Secret `pcap-analyzer-secrets` key `openai-api-key`\n\n#### Scenario: Environment variables for AgentCube endpoints\n\n- **GIVEN** the deployment container spec\n- **WHEN** the pod starts\n- **THEN** environment variables `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL`, `OPENAI_API_BASE`, `OPENAI_MODEL`, `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME`, `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE`, and `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` SHALL be set with deployment-specific values\n\n#### Scenario: Container command matches local\n\n- **GIVEN** the deployment container spec\n- **WHEN** Kubernetes launches the container\n- **THEN** the command SHALL be `[\"uv\"]` with args `[\"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]`, identical to local Docker execution\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Response schema\n\nThe system SHALL define a Pydantic response model for the analyze endpoint.\n\n#### Scenario: AnalyzeResponse structure\n\n- **GIVEN** a successful analysis completion\n- **WHEN** the endpoint returns\n- **THEN** the response SHALL match `AnalyzeResponse` with fields `script: str`, `results: List[Dict[str, Any]]`, and `report: str`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Error handling patterns\n\nThe system SHALL handle execution failures gracefully and surface meaningful errors to clients.\n\n#### Scenario: CommandExecutionError handling\n\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox command that returns non-zero exit code\n- **WHEN** `execute_command` raises `CommandExecutionError`\n- **THEN** the analysis loop SHALL capture the error, pass results to `_repair_script`, and retry if under the limit\n\n#### Scenario: Max retries exceeded\n\n- **GIVEN** script execution fails after `max_retries` attempts\n- **WHEN** the final repair attempt also fails\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL raise `HTTPException(status_code=500, detail=f\"Sandbox error: {e.stderr}\")`\n\n---\n\n## Constants Summary\n\n| Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n|----------|-------|------|---------|\n| `SERVER_HOST` | `\"0.0.0.0\"` | `pcap_analyzer.py` | HTTP bind address |\n| `SERVER_PORT` | `8000` | `pcap_analyzer.py` | HTTP listen port |\n| `SERVER_RELOAD` | `True` | `pcap_analyzer.py` | Development auto-reload |\n| `DEFAULT_API_BASE` | `\"https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1\"` | `pcap_analyzer.py` | OpenAI-compatible API base |\n| `DEFAULT_MODEL` | `\"Qwen/QwQ-32B\"` | `pcap_analyzer.py` | Default LLM model |\n| `DEFAULT_INTERPRETER_NAME` | `\"my-interpreter\"` | `pcap_analyzer.py` | Sandbox interpreter name |\n| `DEFAULT_NAMESPACE` | `\"default\"` | `pcap_analyzer.py` | Kubernetes namespace |\n| `DEFAULT_WARMUP_SEC` | `5` | `pcap_analyzer.py` | Sandbox warmup duration |\n| `MAX_RETRIES` | `2` | `pcap_analyzer.py` | Script repair retry limit |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies Summary\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `fastapi` | `0.120.0` | Web framework |\n| `uvicorn` | `0.38.0` | ASGI server |\n| `langchain` | `1.0.2` | LLM orchestration |\n| `langchain-openai` | `1.0.1` | OpenAI-compatible integration |\n| `langgraph` | `1.0.1` | Agent graph framework |\n| `langgraph-prebuilt` | `1.0.1` | Prebuilt ReAct agent pattern |\n| `python-multipart` | `0.0.20` | Form/file upload support |\n| `agentcube` | (vendored) | AgentCube SDK for sandbox |\n\n---\n\n## File Changes Summary\n\n| File | Action | Description |\n|------|--------|-------------|\n| `example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py` | create | FastAPI app with SandboxRunner, agents, /analyze endpoint |\n| `example/pcap-analyzer/requirements.txt` | create | LangChain, FastAPI, and supporting dependencies |\n| `example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile` | create | `uv`-based image with vendored SDK |\n| `example/pcap-analyzer/deployment.yaml` | create | K8s Deployment with Secret and env wiring |\n| `example/pcap-analyzer/README.md` | create | Usage and deployment documentation |\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- python-sdk/design.md — AgentCube SDK design\n- python-sdk/spec.md — AgentCube SDK specification\n- integrations/design.md — Extended integrations architecture\n- integrations/spec.md — PCAP analyzer requirements (shared)\n\n---\n\n## Validation Checklist\n\n- [ ] Application fails startup without `OPENAI_API_KEY`\n- [ ] `POST /analyze` accepts `pcap_file` upload\n- [ ] `POST /analyze` accepts `pcap_path` form field\n- [ ] `POST /analyze` returns 400 when neither input provided\n- [ ] `SandboxRunner` wraps `CodeInterpreterClient` correctly\n- [ ] `SandboxRunner.upload_file` stages files in sandbox\n- [ ] `SandboxRunner.run` executes commands and returns structured output\n- [ ] `SandboxRunner.stop` cleans up sessions\n- [ ] PLANNER agent generates executable Python scripts\n- [ ] `_analyze_with_retries` retries on execution failure\n- [ ] REPORTER agent synthesizes results into report\n- [ ] Environment defaults match constants\n- [ ] Dockerfile uses `uv` and vendors SDK\n- [ ] Deployment manifest sets resources and secrets correctly\n- [ ] `AnalyzeResponse` schema matches endpoint output"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sdk-python/examples/agent_runtime_usage.py":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-037/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-037/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775893737044,"end":1775893737067}}}}
